BOKOSHE PUBLIC SCHOOL ON-SITE COVID PROCEDURES
COVID classroom procedures will involve having assigned seating and maintaining social distancing. We
recommend that you wear a mask when social distancing is not possible. Masks can consist of commercially made,
medical, homemade, neck gaiters, etc. It is highly recommended that you have one on your person while in the
classroom or in the hallways. It is better to have one and not need it than need it and not have it. Should a person
not have a mask and wants one, the school will be able to provide one. If we all behave in a responsible, respectful
manner in regard to how COVID affects all of us, we will be successful in creating a positive… More

Just a reminder to the Bokoshe Community:

The Girl Scout Troop 4097 is still running the Free Public Library. It is located in the large silver cabinet outside the city hall. All books are free to take, you many also leave a book if you would like. We have a lot of new books to put in there, but no room to do so. Please check out our selection and take a book home today.

Thank you, the Bokoshe Girl Scouts.

post_text: Emily Carver, the FCCLA State VP of Programs, attended the OKC Thunder Leadership Workshop in Oklahoma City this week. She volunteered at the Toby Keith Kid's Corral which provides a place to stay for the parents of pediatric cancer patients. In two weeks, she will be traveling to the State Capital to speak to representatives about career tech education.

post_text:
November 5, 2018

Parents and Guardians,

Bokoshe Schools will not have school tomorrow, November 6. The funeral for K J Yates, a former student of Bokoshe, will be held in our gym tomorrow morning at 10:00 am. We will make-up this day on some Friday after Christmas.

If you want information from our school sent directly to your phone, you can join our school wide message system by texting "@bokoshe" to "81010". We currently have 83 people connected to this service and would like everyone to join.

We appreciate your understanding and thank you for allowing us to educate your child.

Sincerely,

David Smith
Superintendent/Principal

November 5, 2018
